1 A RESOLUTION honoring Harriet Thompson of Winchester, Kentucky, for her
2 service to her community and the Clark County Republican Women’s Club.
3 WHEREAS, Harriet Thompson was born in Clark County Kentucky, in 1946 and
4 has lived there her entire life; and
5 WHEREAS, Harriet Thompson worked for United States Department of Labor for
6 nearly 23 years before eventually retiring in 2008; and
7 WHEREAS, Harriet Thompson has demonstrated outstanding dedication and
8 faithful service to the Clark County Republican Women’s Club over the course of many
9 years; and
10 WHEREAS, throughout her tenure, she has selflessly served in multiple leadership
11 roles, including Club Treasurer and Second Vice President, carrying out each
12 responsibility with integrity, diligence, and professionalism; and
13 WHEREAS, Harriet Thompson is widely known for her unwavering loyalty to the
14 Republican Party and her consistent willingness to assist in any capacity needed, always
15 answering the call to serve without hesitation; and
16 WHEREAS, her dependable leadership, strong worth ethic, and servant's heart have
17 significantly strengthened the mission, unity, and effectiveness of the Clark County
18 Republican Women's Club; and
19 WHEREAS, Harriet Thompson's exemplary commitment, positive spirit, and
20 steadfast support have earned her the deep respect and gratitude of her fellow members
21 and the broader Republican community;
22 NOW, THEREFORE,
23 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
24 Kentucky:
25 Section 1. The Senate honors Harriet Thompson for her years of exceptional
26 service, leadership, and loyalty, and extends its sincere appreciation for her invaluable
27 contributions to the Clark County Republican Women's Club and to the Republican
